<!-- FAQ Help --><div class="help-section"><nav class="help-breadcrumb"><a href="/help">Help</a> / <span>FAQ</span></nav><h1><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Frequently Asked Questions</h1><p class="help-intro">Common questions and answers.</p><div class="faq-list"><div class="faq-item"><h3>Q: Do I need accounting experience to use this?</h3><p>A: No! The app is designed for nonprofit volunteers and staff. Basic financial concepts are explained in the help documentation and glossary.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Q: What's the difference between Categories and Accounts?</h3><p>A: <strong>Categories</strong> classify WHAT the money is for (Equipment, Training, Donations). <strong>Accounts</strong> track WHERE the money is held (General Fund, Building Fund). Every transaction has both.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Q: How do I handle restricted donations?</h3><p>A: Create an Account (Fund) for that purpose, mark it as "Restricted", and assign donations to that account. The system will track restricted vs unrestricted funds separately.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Q: Can multiple people use this at the same time?</h3><p>A: The current version is designed for single-user or small team use on one computer. Enterprise multi-user versions are available.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Q: How do I generate tax receipts for donors?</h3><p>A: Go to Donors, select the donor, and click "Generate Tax Receipt". The system creates a receipt showing all donations for the year.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Q: What Form 990 do we need to file?</h3><p>A: It depends on your gross receipts: Under $50K = 990-N (e-Postcard), Under $200K with assets under $500K = 990-EZ, Otherwise = Full 990. See the <a href="/help/form990">Form 990 Guide</a>.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Q: How often should I backup?</h3><p>A: At minimum weekly, preferably daily. Enable automatic backups in Settings for peace of mind.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Q: Can I import data from QuickBooks or Excel?</h3><p>A: Yes! Go to Import/Export and use the CSV import feature. See <a href="/help/importexport">Import/Export Help</a> for format details.</p></div></div></div>
